el gran número de impactos (frecuencia de colisión en líquidos ) con las moléculas del líquido en que están inmersos.\n","\n","2) El movimiento de las moléculas es tan complicado que sólo se puede describir probabilísticamente en términos de un gran número de impactos independientes\n","\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"xMJtn4IN1tLu"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Se realizara una simulacion en base a la ecuacion de langevin simplificada. Esta empieza suponiendo por leyes de newton, las fuerzas que actuan en cada una de las particulas:\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","![Screenshot 2023-11-19 16.32.45.png](data:image/png;base64,)"],"metadata":{"id":"XUgOAcwe3BxG"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["dim = 3 #sistema tridimensional\n","nparticulas = 100 #numero de particulas(nump)\n","n = 1024 #pasos en la simulacion o fotogramas(nums)\n","dt = 0.05 #incremento en el tiempo\n","miuf = 1.0 #costante de friccion(zeta)\n","m = 1 #masa de las particulas\n","temp = 1  #temperaturas de las particulas(kbt)\n","std = np.sqrt(2*temp*miuf*dt) #desviacion estandar de distribucion de impulsos\n","box = 80"],"metadata":{"id":"AbDv9WAdqCwq","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700491059330,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":7,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}}},"execution_count":2,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["np.random.seed(0)\n","  #arreglos tridimensionale spara almacenar temporalmente datos en un dt\n","R = np.zeros([nparticulas,dim])      #posicion\n","V = np.zeros([nparticulas,dim])       #velocidad\n","W = np.zeros([nparticulas,dim])       #impulsos\n","\n"," #arreglos alamvenan los datos de todas la sparticulas para cada n\n","Rt = np.zeros([n ,nparticulas,dim]) #posicion de todas las particulas\n","Vt = np.zeros([n ,nparticulas,dim]) #velocidad de todas las particulas\n","Wt = np.zeros([n ,nparticulas,dim]) #impulsos de todas las particulas\n","\n","time = np.zeros([n]) #pasos"],"metadata":{"id":"eg0j_jOKNvnd","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700491061578,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}}},"execution_count":3,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["for i in range(n):\n","  W = std*np.random.randn(nparticulas,dim)  #fuerzas aleatorias para cada particula\n","  R , V = R + V*dt , V*(1-miuf/m*dt) + W/m  #ecuaciones de movimiento\n","  Rt[i , : , :] = R\n","  Vt[i , : , :] = V     #almacenamiento de las posiciones\n","  Wt[i , : , :] = W\n","  time[i] = i*dt"],"metadata":{"id":"r1mJE8NuOoTg","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700491063815,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":283,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}}},"execution_count":4,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (4,4))\n","ax.set_xlabel(\"Rx\")\n","ax.set_ylabel(\"Ry\")\n","plt.xlim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","plt.ylim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","for n in range(nparticulas):\n","  ax.plot(Rt[:,n,0] , Rt[:,n,1] , alpha = 0.5)\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":393},"id":"Wk1To7r_SsmE","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700491067706,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":2028,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"outputId":"4ce6b7de-8f5f-4aae-d908-79f5cc827a5a"},"execution_count":5,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["fig = plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))\n","ax = fig.add_subplot(111 , projection =\"3d\")\n","\n","ax.set_xlim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","ax.set_ylim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","ax.set_zlim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","\n","ax.set_xlabel(\"Rx\")\n","ax.set_ylabel(\"Ry\")\n","ax.set_zlabel(\"Rz\")\n","\n","ax.view_init(elev=12 , azim=120) #punto de vista\n","for n in range(nparticulas):\n","  ax.plot(Rt[:,n,0] , Rt[:,n,1] , Rt[:,n,2] , alpha = 0.5)\n","plt.show"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":440},"id":"dST7dwl6UXec","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700491079617,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":5484,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"outputId":"e0786504-aa07-4183-aa1e-1608507b7082"},"execution_count":7,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["<function matplotlib.pyplot.show(close=None, block=None)>"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":7},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 500x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def init():\n","    global R, V, W, Rt, Vt, Wt, time\n","    R[:, :], V[:, :], W[:, :] = 0.0, 0.0, 0.0\n","    Rt[:, :, :], Vt[:, :, :], Wt[:, :, :] = 0.0, 0.0, 0.0\n","    time[:] = 0.0\n","    #title.set_text(\"Movimiento Browniano\")\n","    particles[0].set_data([], [])\n","    particles[0].set_3d_properties([])\n","    return particles[0] ,title"],"metadata":{"id":"xzPYBVdvWCIB","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700491081046,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}}},"execution_count":8,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def animate(i):\n","    global R, V, W, Rt, Vt, time\n","    time[i] = i * dt\n","    W = std * np.random.randn(nparticulas, dim)\n","    R, V = R + V * dt, V * (1 - miuf / m * dt) + W / m\n","    Rt[i, :, :] = R\n","    Vt[i, :, :] = V\n","    Wt[i, :, :] = W\n","    #title.set_text(\"Movimiento Browniano\")\n","    particles[0].set_data(R[:, 0], R[:, 1])\n","    particles[0].set_3d_properties(R[:, 2])\n","    return particles[0]  , title"],"metadata":{"id":"cRcbM2wDZI7P","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700491082610,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}}},"execution_count":9,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#PARAMETROS DE INICIALIZACION\n","dim = 3 #sistema tridimensional\n","nparticulas = 500 #numero de particulas(nump)\n","n = 2024 #pasos en la simulacion o fotogramas(nums)\n","\n","np.random.seed(0)\n","R = np.zeros([nparticulas,dim])\n","V = np.zeros([nparticulas,dim])\n","W = np.zeros([nparticulas,dim])\n","Rt = np.zeros([n ,nparticulas,dim])\n","Vt = np.zeros([n ,nparticulas,dim])\n","Wt = np.zeros([n ,nparticulas,dim])\n","time = np.zeros([n]) #pasos"],"metadata":{"id":"TVoe3FDkbu7n"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#simulacion y animar\n","box = 50\n","fig = plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))\n","ax = fig.add_subplot(111 , projection =\"3d\")\n","\n","ax.set_xlim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","ax.set_ylim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","ax.set_zlim(-box/2 , box/2)\n","\n","ax.set_xlabel(\"Rx\")\n","ax.set_ylabel(\"Ry\")\n","ax.set_zlabel(\"Rz\")\n","\n","ax.view_init(elev=12 , azim=120) #punto de vista\n","\n","particles = ax.plot([],[],[], \"ro\" , ms = 8 , alpha = 0.5)\n","title = ax.text(-180 , 0 , 270 , r\"\" , transform = ax.transAxes , va = \"center\")\n","s = 0 #trayectoria e la n-sima particula\n","anim = animation.FuncAnimation(fig ,func=animate , init_func = init , frames = n , interval = 8 , blit = True , repeat = False )\n","HTML(anim.to_html5_video())"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":926,"output_embedded_package_id":"17ljhrlJbXhXPTn647fCKAV7zk4rvdOiM"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700423735550,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":157582,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"outputId":"e273be96-ebc2-4501-a883-0d8747c3c62b","id":"MEOQ__58cewb"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"Output hidden; open in https://colab.research.google.com to view."},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["La teorìa cinético-molecular, también llamada teoría cinética de los gases, se basa en la idea de que todos los gases se comportan de la misma manera en lo referente al movimiento molecular.\n","La teoría cinética de los gases utiliza una descripción molecular para explicar el comportamiento macroscópico de la materia basada en los mismos postulados dados por einstein para el movimiento browniano.\n","\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"Ds6rl_qQ3psa"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Teniendo en cuenta que es un proceso completamente estocastico,  podemos definir una función de distribución de las velocidades moleculares , ya que, con un número finito de moléculas, la probabilidad de que una molécula tenga exactamente una velocidad determinada es cero.\n","Pues , las partículas probablemente tendrán varias velocidades. En lugar de enumerar la velocidad de cada molécula de gas individual, podemos combinar estas velocidades individuales de varias maneras para obtener velocidades “colectivas” que describen la muestra como un todo.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"aARHeQWs34U4"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##DISTRIBUCION DE BOLTZMAN"],"metadata":{"id":"06XusXoW_Hhc"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["La distribucion de maxwell-boltzmann es esa distribucion de velocidades que nos ayuda a tener conocimiento sobre las energia y velocidad de las moleculas de un gas ideal que se comportan aleatoriamente, en un movimiento browniano.\n","Esta està definida por:\n","![Screenshot 2023-11-19 17.31.10.png](data:image/png;base64,)"],"metadata":{"id":"sti-xr834GFj"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Vemos entonces que esta funcion depende tanto de la masa como de la temperatura en la cual se encuentren estas particulas. Dados ciertos valores de masa y temperatura, podemos determinar sobre el comportamiento de las particulas que:"],"metadata":{"id":"OzUkYrnO4z87"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Distribucion MAxwell -Boltzman\n","def MaxwellBoltzman(v,T):\n","    kB = 1.38e-23\n","    m = 500*1.66e-27\n","    return (m/(2*np.pi*kB*T))**1.5 * 4*np.pi * v**2 * np.exp(-m*v**2/(2*kB*T))\n","\n","fig = plt.figure()\n","ax = fig.add_subplot(111)\n","\n","v = np.arange(0,800,1)\n","i , colors = 0 , [\"#F2F909\" ,\"#F99A09\", \"#F96409\",\"red\"]\n","for T in [100,200,300,400]:\n","  fv = MaxwellBoltzman(v,T)\n","  ax.plot(v,fv,label='T='+str(T)+' K', lw=2 , color = colors[i])\n","  i += 1\n","\n","ax.legend(loc=0)\n","ax.set_xlabel('(m/s)')\n","ax.set_ylabel('n/N')\n","fig.suptitle(\"Distribucion de Velocidades Maxweel-Boltzmann\")\n","plt.title(\"variacion en la temperatura\" , style = \"italic\" , fontsize = 10)\n","plt.xlim(0,300)\n","plt.text(220 ,0.01 , f\"m = 8.3x10-25kg \")\n","plt.draw()\n","plt.grid()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":497},"id":"cwjb5jS-ANhd","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700417155471,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":2694,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"outputId":"844bdb7f-7d26-4d53-ec74-573a6a354436"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["1) Las temperaturas más altas permiten que una mayor fracción de moléculas adquieran mayores cantidades de energía cinética, lo que provoca que las parcelas de Boltzmann se extiendan. A temperaturas más bajas, las moléculas tienen menos energía. Por lo tanto, las velocidades de las moléculas son menores y la distribución tiene un rango menor. A medida que aumenta la temperatura de las moléculas, la distribución se aplana. Debido a que las moléculas tienen mayor energía a mayor temperatura, las moléculas se mueven más rápido"],"metadata":{"id":"h4aCEVvYlfEQ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def MaxwellBoltzman(v,m):\n","    kB = 1.38e-23\n","    T = 300\n","    return (m/(2*np.pi*kB*T))**1.5 * 4*np.pi * v**2 * np.exp(-m*v**2/(2*kB*T))\n","\n","m = 500*1.66e-27\n","fig = plt.figure()\n","ax = fig.add_subplot(111)\n","\n","v = np.arange(0,800,1)\n","i , colors = 1 , [\"#FAAB97\" ,\"#F78708\", \"#E03D13\",\"red\"]\n","for m in [m,2*m,3*m,4*m]:\n","  fv = MaxwellBoltzman(v,m)\n","  ax.plot( v, fv, label=f\"{i}m Kg\" , lw=2 , color = colors[i-1])\n","  i += 1\n","\n","ax.legend(loc=0)\n","ax.set_xlabel('(m/s)')\n","ax.set_ylabel('n/N')\n","fig.suptitle(\"Distribucion de Velocidades Maxweel-Boltzmann\")\n","plt.title(f\"variacion en la masa \" , style = \"italic\" , fontsize = 10)\n","plt.text(250 ,0.01 , f\"m = 8.3x10-25kg \")\n","plt.text(250 ,0.011 , f\"T = 300 K \")\n","plt.xlim(0,300)\n","plt.draw()\n","plt.grid()"],"metadata":{"id":"s-JS3GtX_O3q","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700417159797,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":1448,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":497},"outputId":"eed46e74-c220-41c3-f6df-991e9a2845cb"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":[" 2) En promedio, las moléculas más pesadas se mueven más lentamente que las moléculas más ligeras. Por lo tanto, las moléculas más pesadas tendrán una distribución de velocidad menor, mientras que las moléculas más ligeras tendrán una distribución de velocidad que está más extendida"],"metadata":{"id":"uC0e_GLslrvK"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Por otro lado, es importante tener en cuenta la velocidad media de la distribucion total, es decir, la velocidad promedio entre todas las particulas del sistema. Ademas, tambien podemos encontrar un valor para la mas probable.\n","\n","la primera por la suma desde 0 a infinito de las velocidades:\n","\n","![Screenshot 2023-11-19 17.38.51.png](data:image/png;base64,)\n","\n","La segunda por el valor maximo que toma la funcion;\n","\n","![Screenshot 2023-11-19 17.37.50.png](data:image/png;base64,)"],"metadata":{"id":"mljF1NPP5XmF"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def MaxwellBoltzmann(v, m , T):\n","      kB = 1.38e-23\n","      return (m/(2*np.pi*kB*T))**1.5 * 4*np.pi * v**2 * np.exp(-m*v**2/(2*kB*T))"],"metadata":{"id":"CKxkhy0V8pOG"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def velocidades(M,t):\n","  funcion = lambda v: -MaxwellBoltzmann(v, m=M , T=t)\n","  funcion2 = lambda v: v*(MaxwellBoltzmann(v, m=M , T=t))\n","  v_prob = minimize_scalar(funcion, bounds=(0, 500))\n","  v_med = sc.quad(funcion2 , 0 , np.inf )[0]\n","\n","  return  [v_prob.x , v_med]\n","\n","a,b = 3.5e-24 , 100\n","v = np.arange(0,800,1)\n","fv = MaxwellBoltzmann(v, a, b)\n","\n","fig = plt.figure()\n","ax = fig.add_subplot(111)\n","ax.plot( v, fv , lw=2 , color = \"orange\")\n","plt.fill_between(v, fv, color='pink', alpha=0.5, label='probabilidad')\n","\n","ax.legend()\n","ax.set_xlabel('(m/s)')\n","ax.set_ylabel('n/N')\n","plt.title(f\"DISTRIBUCION DE MAXWELL-BOLTZMANN \")\n","plt.axvline(int(velocidades(a,b)[0]) , color='red', linestyle='--', label='velocidad mas probable')\n","plt.axvline(int(velocidades(a,b)[1]) , color='red', linestyle='--', label='velocidad media')\n","plt.xlim(0,200)\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.draw()\n","plt.grid()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":472},"id":"W6fEfrM09BAI","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700433330722,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":463,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"outputId":"ffc9f88c-0d93-4c77-bc65-e0000832ccae"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def v_masprob(M,t):\n","    funcion = lambda v: -MaxwellBoltzmann(v, m=M , T=t)\n","    funcion2 = lambda v: v*(MaxwellBoltzmann(v, m=M , T=t))\n","\n","    v_prob = minimize_scalar(funcion, bounds=(0, 500))\n","    v_med = sc.quad(funcion2 , 0 , np.inf )[0]\n","\n","    return f\"\"\"la velocidad mas probable de una particula cualquiera es {round(v_prob.x,2)} m/s y la velocidad promedio de la distribucion es de {round(v_med,2)} m/s\"\"\""],"metadata":{"id":"pLWHzBiOfpu_"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["v_masprob( 500*1.66e-27 , 300)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":36},"id":"H364du6lpckW","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700421127348,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":260,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"outputId":"619fe835-6e5f-4707-d5a7-02c8d6992295"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["'la velocidad mas probable de una particula cualquiera es 99.88 m/s y la velocidad promedio de la distribucion es de 112.7 m/s'"],"application/vnd.google.colaboratory.intrinsic+json":{"type":"string"}},"metadata":{},"execution_count":63}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ademas, el area bajo la curva*100 de la funcion, define la probabilidad de medir un valor cualquiera de velocidad para una particula cualquiera, pudiendo asi calcular la probabilidad como:\n","\n","![Screenshot 2023-11-19 17.45.30.png](data:image/png;base64,)"],"metadata":{"id":"uy1k6BJ-6yDQ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def probabilidad(M, t ,v1 , v2):\n","  funcion = lambda v: (MaxwellBoltzmann(v, m=M , T=t))\n","  prob = sc.quad(funcion , v1 , v2 )[0]\n","  return f\"La probabilidad de que la velocidad de una particula cualquiera este entre {v1}m/s y {v2}m/s es de {abs(round(prob*100,2))}%\""],"metadata":{"id":"AcPM5Biku_Bp"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["probabilidad(500*1.66e-27 , 300 , 50 , 150)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":36},"id":"T5Br1VO-8HMu","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1700421132066,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":235,"user":{"displayName":"SOFIA MOSCOSO ORTIZ","userId":"16663054995924911074"}},"outputId":"5c1ab8bf-f299-4bbc-f72f-7968268996e9"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["'La probabilidad de que la velocidad de una particula cualquiera este entre 50m/s y 150m/s es de 70.73%'"],"application/vnd.google.colaboratory.intrinsic+json":{"type":"string"}},"metadata":{},"execution_count":65}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Por ultimo, cuando se conoce la cantidad total de particulas en la muestra, podemos definir la cantidad de particulas esperada que tiene una velocidad cualquiera asi:\n","\n","![Screenshot 2023-11-19 17.42.04.png](data:image/png;base64,)"],"metadata":{"id":"lfeoZM6g7R__"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def particulas_espe(M, t ,v1 , v2 , N): #N es el numero total de particulas\n","  funcion = lambda v: (MaxwellBoltzmann(v, m=M , T=t))\n","  esperadas = N*(sc.quad(funcion , v1 , v2 )[0])\n","  return f\"Las cantidad de particulas esperadas con una velocidad entre {v1}m/s y {v2}m/s es de {abs(round(esperadas,2))}\""],"metadata":{"id":"pAAmFLejyk5e"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}